"{\"uid\": \"straitstimes.com-sport-under-a-soft-rain-at-the-paris-olympics-hardy-rowers-use-the-power-of-words\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Choose edition  Search  singapore  asia  world  opinion  life  business  sport  Visual  Podcasts  SPH Rewards  STClassifieds  Paid press releases  Advertise with us  FAQs  Contact us  Sporting Life  Sign up now:Get the biggest sports news in your inbox  Singapore rower Saiyidah Aisyah scribbles words in her journal, a sort of raw accounting of her days.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 355, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 98, \"end\": 101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.564106081516482e-14, \"text\": \"SPH\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\"}, {\"begin\": 147, \"end\": 156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\", \"score\": 0.9604822703099307, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Advertise\", \"types\": [\"Q7377\", \"Q729\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\"}, {\"begin\": 254, \"end\": 263, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2863140210991538e-13, \"text\": \"Singapore\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\"}, {\"begin\": 270, \"end\": 285, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saiyidah_Aisyah\", \"score\": 0.9999999999131433, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Saiyidah Aisyah\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saiyidah_Aisyah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saiyidah_Aisyah\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"ST PHOTO: MARK CHEONG  Rohit Brijnath  Published\\u00c2Jul 27, 2024, 11:04 PM  Updated\\u00c2Jul 28, 2024, 01:21 AM  PARIS\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093The name of a stranger from a foreign land is written on a sticker in Jacob Plihal\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s boat.\", \"from\": 357, \"to\": 562, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 380, \"end\": 394, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rohit_Brijnath\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rohit Brijnath\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rohit_Brijnath\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rohit_Brijnath\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cKim,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d it says.\", \"from\": 564, \"to\": 583, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She isn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t Plihal\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s friend, she isn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t family.\", \"from\": 585, \"to\": 635, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This polite, 2.08m American hasn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t even ever met the Australian.\", \"from\": 636, \"to\": 702, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 655, \"end\": 663, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999996045313182, \"rank\": 3.272839458236619e-07, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 691, \"end\": 701, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.5761816925791777, \"rank\": 0.7355635702910049, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But under a gently pecking rain at the Vaires-sur-Marne Nautical Stadium in Paris, as we discuss motivation, this 28-year-old with an architectural degree mentions her name.\", \"from\": 703, \"to\": 876, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 742, \"end\": 758, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vaires-sur-Marne\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6033920135177186e-16, \"text\": \"Vaires-sur-Marne\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vaires-sur-Marne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vaires-sur-Marne\"}, {\"begin\": 779, \"end\": 784, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1987406156244757e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll put little stickers in my boat sometimes,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d explains Plihal.\", \"from\": 878, \"to\": 949, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cLike a little mantra that\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s been impactful lately.\", \"from\": 950, \"to\": 1005, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So one that comes to mind is just a name, Kim Brennan.\", \"from\": 1006, \"to\": 1060, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1048, \"end\": 1059, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Brennan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kim Brennan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Brennan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Brennan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cShe was an Australian rower, single sculler, very successful, won (gold at) the 2016 Olympics.\", \"from\": 1062, \"to\": 1159, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1076, \"end\": 1086, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.5761816925791777, \"rank\": 0.7355635702910049, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And I think she\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s a very good influence on technique.\", \"from\": 1160, \"to\": 1215, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So just writing \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cKim\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d in my boat, I see that and I visualise how she rows and that\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s someone I try to model (myself on).\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  These Games are fiercer than we can imagine and races unfold like hasty, unforgiving interrogations.\", \"from\": 1216, \"to\": 1447, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Just to make it clear, the Italian fencer Luigi Samele put it bluntly: \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThe goal of the Olympics, of course, is not to have a nice walk around the Olympic Village, but to go home with medals\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d.\", \"from\": 1448, \"to\": 1644, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1475, \"end\": 1482, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"score\": 0.9716214844063344, \"rank\": 0.025869301005112484, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1490, \"end\": 1502, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Luigi_Samele_(fencer)\", \"score\": 0.9999983145058302, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Luigi Samele\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Luigi_Samele_(fencer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Luigi_Samele_(fencer)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But in this festival committed to the athletic deeds, don\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t underestimate the power of words.\", \"from\": 1646, \"to\": 1741, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Coaches in Paris shout them.\", \"from\": 1742, \"to\": 1770, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1753, \"end\": 1758, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1987406156244757e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Psychologists use them as balm.\", \"from\": 1771, \"to\": 1802, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Athletes mutter them in call rooms.\", \"from\": 1803, \"to\": 1838, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And sometimes, as with former medal-winning gymnast Louis Smith, they even tattoo reminders onto their arms: \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cWhat I Deserve I Earn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d.\", \"from\": 1839, \"to\": 1976, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1891, \"end\": 1902, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_Smith_(gymnast)\", \"score\": 0.7117012252196068, \"rank\": 0.4031850353893259, \"text\": \"Louis Smith\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_Smith_(gymnast)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_Smith_(gymnast)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Singapore rower Saiyidah Aisyah scribbles words in her journal, a sort of raw accounting of her days.\", \"from\": 1978, \"to\": 2079, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1978, \"end\": 1987, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2863140210991538e-13, \"text\": \"Singapore\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\"}, {\"begin\": 1994, \"end\": 2009, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saiyidah_Aisyah\", \"score\": 0.9999999999131433, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Saiyidah Aisyah\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saiyidah_Aisyah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saiyidah_Aisyah\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Words to rise to and go to sleep with.\", \"from\": 2080, \"to\": 2118, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Words to wear like armour.\", \"from\": 2119, \"to\": 2145, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Words that before Rio 2016 \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 the first Olympics she qualified for \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 she pasted to her wall almost in the thousands.\", \"from\": 2146, \"to\": 2265, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Some were truths, some a plea, some an athletic prayer.\", \"from\": 2266, \"to\": 2321, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cTrain to be bulletproof\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d.\", \"from\": 2323, \"to\": 2353, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt is meant to be hard\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d.\", \"from\": 2355, \"to\": 2384, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI am *&^%^& amazing.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  This year, making a comeback after stepping away from the sport, Aisyah turned to words again.\", \"from\": 2386, \"to\": 2508, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Filled her journal with scribbles as if writing them down was reassurance.\", \"from\": 2509, \"to\": 2583, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Just before the Games she shared two pages of them with The Straits Times.\", \"from\": 2584, \"to\": 2658, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2640, \"end\": 2657, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Straits_Times\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"The Straits Times\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Straits_Times\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Straits_Times\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI am strong, lifting heavy at the gym, 11 on the chin ups.\", \"from\": 2660, \"to\": 2721, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Powerful.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI have done this before.\", \"from\": 2722, \"to\": 2763, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Trust.\", \"from\": 2764, \"to\": 2770, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Let go.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI know what pain feels like.\", \"from\": 2771, \"to\": 2814, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I feel it every day out there on water.\", \"from\": 2815, \"to\": 2854, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is nothing different.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Incredibly after barely a year back, Aisyah qualified for Paris but on July 27, under a sulky grey sky, she couldn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t find her best self.\", \"from\": 2855, \"to\": 3024, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2944, \"end\": 2949, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1987406156244757e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In Rio, in her quarter-finals, she timed 7min 56sec across 2,000m; in Paris,in the heats where she came fifth out of five competitors, she stopped the clock at 8:17.04.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI know what I can do,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d she said later, being unsparing with her words \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cand I did not do it today.\", \"from\": 3025, \"to\": 3299, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3028, \"end\": 3031, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999999999947704, \"rank\": 5.2226981743670783e-11, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 3095, \"end\": 3100, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1987406156244757e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The power was just not there.\", \"from\": 3300, \"to\": 3329, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The speed was not there.\", \"from\": 3330, \"to\": 3354, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Rowing is simple.\", \"from\": 3355, \"to\": 3372, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s just put the blades in and take the blades out.\", \"from\": 3373, \"to\": 3427, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And sometimes you may make it more complicated.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Rowers embody strength, as if they\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re massive human engines fitted neatly into slim boats.\", \"from\": 3428, \"to\": 3572, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But these gleaming bodies, these flat, competitive faces, are partly lies.\", \"from\": 3573, \"to\": 3647, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In sport, toughness always resides beside insecurity.\", \"from\": 3648, \"to\": 3701, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Behind everyone\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s fibre, doubt rustles.\", \"from\": 3702, \"to\": 3743, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009c(I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m) definitely trying to keep strong, positive thoughts,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d says Olympic first-timer Paige Badenhorst of South Africa.\", \"from\": 3745, \"to\": 3870, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3837, \"end\": 3842, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paige_Smith\", \"score\": 0.9999967014496011, \"rank\": 3.2552871366608783e-06, \"text\": \"Paige\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paige_Smith\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paige_Smith\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cAcknowledging the demons that, yes, I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m nervous, everyone else is nervous.\", \"from\": 3871, \"to\": 3950, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But also reminding myself of my strengths, what you do have that will help you fight those demons.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  To ward off these demons is to reach for words.\", \"from\": 3951, \"to\": 4101, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"To remind themselves of who they are.\", \"from\": 4102, \"to\": 4139, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What they\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ve done.\", \"from\": 4140, \"to\": 4160, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"How they\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ve earned their way here.\", \"from\": 4161, \"to\": 4197, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And so Badenhorst, part of the 2022 Cambridge crew who won the annual Boat Race on the River Thames, has words echoing in her head.\", \"from\": 4198, \"to\": 4329, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cCalm.\", \"from\": 4331, \"to\": 4339, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Cool.\", \"from\": 4340, \"to\": 4345, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Collected.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cFierce.\", \"from\": 4346, \"to\": 4371, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ruthless.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cJust repeat those words to myself.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  During a race?\", \"from\": 4372, \"to\": 4442, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cBefore, during, after,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d she says with laugh.\", \"from\": 4444, \"to\": 4493, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s not just her, it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s champions who reach for words to achieve that perfect state they\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re searching for.\", \"from\": 4495, \"to\": 4611, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Emma Twigg, 37, is the defending Olympic champion in the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s single sculls, has a licence to skipper boats, can repair cycles and has an academic degree in sports.\", \"from\": 4612, \"to\": 4781, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4612, \"end\": 4622, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Twigg\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emma Twigg\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Twigg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Twigg\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Still for all this, for all her four Games before Paris, she needs to talk to herself at the start.\", \"from\": 4782, \"to\": 4881, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4832, \"end\": 4837, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1987406156244757e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cYou\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ve done this a million times.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Twigg is surging forward, Aisyah has one more chance on July 28 in the repechage.\", \"from\": 4883, \"to\": 5007, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s me just against myself and whatever is in my head,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d she said a little mournfully.\", \"from\": 5008, \"to\": 5101, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s no guarantee in sport, but there is one thing you can be sure she did after her race.\", \"from\": 5102, \"to\": 5197, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She went back to the Village.\", \"from\": 5199, \"to\": 5228, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Pulled out her journal.\", \"from\": 5229, \"to\": 5252, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And found some refuge in words.\", \"from\": 5253, \"to\": 5284, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sporting Life  Olympics 2024  Singapore athletes  Rowing  Team Singapore  E-paper  Newsletters  Podcasts  RSS Feed  About Us  Terms & Conditions  Personal Data Protection Notice  Need help?\", \"from\": 5286, \"to\": 5475, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5316, \"end\": 5325, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2863140210991538e-13, \"text\": \"Singapore\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Reach us here.\", \"from\": 5476, \"to\": 5490, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertise with us\", \"from\": 5492, \"to\": 5509, \"entities\": []}]}"